<img width="107" height="107" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/china-us-107x107.gif?resize=107%2C107&#038;ssl=1" alt="US axes tariffs on Chinese goods in trade war thaw" align="left" style="margin: 0 20px 20px 0;max-width:100%" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The United States and China announced a major thaw in their trade war Friday, including immediate cuts to punishing import tariffs, but a lack of detail left markets cautious. “We have agreed to a very large Phase One Deal with China,” President Donald Trump tweeted after officials in Beijing made a similar announcement. The news could be a boon to Trump, who has made trade wars a keystone of his foreign policy, just as a congressional committee set up a full vote on his impeachment next week for alleged abuse of office. Continue reading US axes tariffs on Chinese goods in trade war thaw at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard